AVIAN INFLUENZA (42): MEXICO, POULTRY, HPAI H7N3, UPDATE, OIE
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 8 Aug 2019
Source: OIE, World Animal Health Information Database (WAHIS) Interface [summarized, edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30012


The following information is related to the current highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) H7N3 situation in Mexico that continues to date (8 Aug 2019).

Mexico continues to have an active event of HPAI H7N3. Since the 1st outbreak was identified in March 2019 until 8 Aug 2019, 22 outbreaks have been reported.

These outbreaks have been detected in the following states: Mexico (2), Jalisco (3), Hidalgo (3), Queretaro (8), Tlaxcala (1), Guerrero (2), Guanajuato (2), and Veracruz (1).

The total affected population is:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 476 092 / 16 632 / 8815 / 154 482 / 138 632

See latest follow-up report no. 7 on 27 Jul 2019 at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=31219.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Mexico has been affected by highly pathogenic avian influenza, subtype H7N3, since June 2012. The following is a summary of the events occurring since 2015:

In 2018 Mexico reported 4 outbreaks of HPAI H7N3. Event summary and map of the event reported in 2018 is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=26143.

Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 4590 / 2985 / 2985 / 1605 / 0

From March 2015 to May 2017 Mexico reported 33 outbreaks of HPAI H7N3. These outbreaks were reported as 2 separated events. See the event summaries and maps for both events below.

Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 361 648 / 20 / 0 / 361648 / 0

Event summaries and maps:
- Event started in March 2015 and resolved in January 2017: 32 outbreaks reported. http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=17489

- Event started in April 2017 and resolved in May 2017: one outbreak reported. http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=23692
- Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Mexico: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6612492,14]
